TITLE: Implementing poll_action for StateFetcher in Rust
DESCRIPTION: Implements the poll_action method for StateFetcher, which determines the next action to take based on queued requests and available peers for block fetching.
SOURCE: https://github.com/paradigmxyz/reth/blob/main/docs/crates/network.md#2025-04-16_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
/// Returns the next action to return
fn poll_action(&mut self) -> PollAction {
    // we only check and not pop here since we don't know yet whether a peer is available.
    if self.queued_requests.is_empty() {
        return PollAction::NoRequests
    }

    let peer_id = if let Some(peer_id) = self.next_peer() {
        peer_id
    } else {
        return PollAction::NoPeersAvailable
    };

    let request = self.queued_requests.pop_front().expect("not empty");
    let request = self.prepare_block_request(peer_id, request);

    PollAction::Ready(FetchAction::BlockRequest { peer_id, request })
}
```

