TITLE: Processing Pending Transactions in Reth's TransactionsManager
DESCRIPTION: This snippet outlines the process of draining the pending_transactions stream in the TransactionsManager's poll method. It collects resolved transactions and calls on_new_transactions for propagation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/paradigmxyz/reth/blob/main/docs/crates/network.md#2025-04-16_snippet_36

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
// Pseudo-code representation of the pending_transactions processing
let mut new_transactions = Vec::new();
while let Some(tx) = self.pending_transactions.poll_next() {
    new_transactions.push(tx);
}
if !new_transactions.is_empty() {
    self.on_new_transactions(new_transactions);
}
```

