TITLE: Configuring Peer Reputation Weights in Reth (TOML)
DESCRIPTION: Defines reputation penalties for various peer misbehaviors in Reth. Penalties are applied to peer reputation scores, with disconnection occurring if the score falls below a threshold. This configuration helps maintain network integrity by discouraging and penalizing malicious behavior.
SOURCE: https://github.com/paradigmxyz/reth/blob/main/book/run/config.md#2025-04-16_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: toml
CODE:
```
[peers.reputation_weights]
bad_message = -16384
bad_block = -16384
bad_transactions = -16384
already_seen_transactions = 0
timeout = -4096
bad_protocol = -2147483648
failed_to_connect = -25600
dropped = -4096
```

