TITLE: Defining DbTxMut Trait in Rust
DESCRIPTION: Defines the DbTxMut trait for read-write transactions, including methods for putting and deleting values, clearing tables, and creating mutable cursors.
SOURCE: https://github.com/paradigmxyz/reth/blob/main/docs/crates/db.md#2025-04-16_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
pub trait DbTxMut: Send + Sync {
    type CursorMut<T: Table>: DbCursorRW<T> + DbCursorRO<T> + Send + Sync;
    type DupCursorMut<T: DupSort>: DbDupCursorRW<T>
        + DbCursorRW<T>
        + DbDupCursorRO<T>
        + DbCursorRO<T>
        + Send
        + Sync;

    fn put<T: Table>(&self, key: T::Key, value: T::Value) -> Result<(), DatabaseError>;
    fn delete<T: Table>(&self, key: T::Key, value: Option<T::Value>) -> Result<bool, DatabaseError>;
    fn clear<T: Table>(&self) -> Result<(), DatabaseError>;
    fn cursor_write<T: Table>(&self) -> Result<Self::CursorMut<T>, DatabaseError>;
    fn cursor_dup_write<T: DupSort>(&self) -> Result<Self::DupCursorMut<T>, DatabaseError>;
}
```

