TITLE: Defining Database Trait in Rust
DESCRIPTION: Defines the main Database trait with associated types for read-only and read-write transactions, and methods for creating and managing these transactions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/paradigmxyz/reth/blob/main/docs/crates/db.md#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
pub trait Database: Send + Sync {
    type TX: DbTx + Send + Sync + Debug + 'static;
    type TXMut: DbTxMut + DbTx + TableImporter + Send + Sync + Debug + 'static;

    #[track_caller]
    fn tx(&self) -> Result<Self::TX, DatabaseError>;

    #[track_caller]
    fn tx_mut(&self) -> Result<Self::TXMut, DatabaseError>;

    fn view<T, F>(&self, f: F) -> Result<T, DatabaseError>
    where
        F: FnOnce(&Self::TX) -> T,
    {
        let tx = self.tx()?;

        let res = f(&tx);
        tx.commit()?;

        Ok(res)
    }

    fn update<T, F>(&self, f: F) -> Result<T, DatabaseError>
    where
        F: FnOnce(&Self::TXMut) -> T,
    {
        let tx = self.tx_mut()?;

        let res = f(&tx);
        tx.commit()?;

        Ok(res)
    }
}
```

